Trump’s budget would cut $9.85M from RI's Supporting Effective Instruction State Grant, which helps school districts pay for #profdev for educators & hire more teachers, resulting in smaller class sizes. Eliminating these funds could cost RI equivalent of 150 teacher salaries.

Trump’s budget would take $5.64 Million from RI’s share of the Student Support and Academic Enrichment Grants. These funds support a variety of critical functions, including improving school conditions, student health and safety, and expanding the use of educational technology.

After-school programs offer hope, opportunity, safety, & student enrichment. But Trump's budget would slash $6M from RI's 21st Century Community Learning Centers funds that support #afterschool programs such as @MyPASA. These cuts would harm kids, working families, & our economy.

Keeping kids safe, fed, enriched & supervised after the school day ends is a smart investment that strengthens communities, helps kids succeed, & provides working parents w/ peace of mind. A big thank you to @MyPASA for their outstanding work & advocacy. #AfterSchoolWorks

I’m inspired by the amazing @MeetStreetNow students & will work to wisely invest in the education and well-being of ALL children, including kids w/ special needs & differing abilities.
